dcterms:description: A comprehensive archive of climate model data used for diagnosing and intercomparing climate models, focusing on precipitation and evapotranspiration data.
dcterms:title: Program for Climate Model Diagnosis and Intercomparison (PCMDI) archive

dcterms:description: Hydrologic data collected by the U.S. Geological Survey, providing information on water use and availability.
dcterms:title: U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) hydrologic data

dcterms:description: Population data sourced from the U.S. Census Bureau, used for estimating future water demand at county levels.
dcterms:title: U.S. Census Bureau population data

dcterms:description: Climate model data from the Coupled Model Intercomparison Project Phase 5, used for assessing future water availability and temperature.
dcterms:title: CMIP5 climate models

dcterms:description: Historical stream temperature data collected by the U.S. Geological Survey, used for analyzing trends in water temperature.
dcterms:title: Historical stream temperature data from USGS

dcterms:description: Data from the Electric Power Research Institute, providing insights into power generation and water use in the energy sector.
dcterms:title: Electric Power Research Institute (EPRI) data

dcterms:description: Data from the Energy Information Administration, detailing energy production and consumption patterns.
dcterms:title: Energy Information Administration (EIA) data

dcterms:description: Data from the National Renewable Energy Laboratory, providing insights into renewable energy resources and technologies.
dcterms:title: National Renewable Energy Laboratory (NREL) data

dcterms:description: Data from the U.S. Historical Climatology Network, providing historical climate data for temperature and precipitation.
dcterms:title: U.S. Historical Climatology Network (USHCN) data

dcterms:description: Global Environment Monitoring System database providing data on environmental conditions, including stream temperature.
dcterms:title: Global Environment Monitoring System (GEMS) database

dcterms:description: Climate model data from the Coupled Model Intercomparison Project Phase 3, used for assessing climate scenarios.
dcterms:title: CMIP3 climate models

dcterms:description: Various climate models and scenarios, including Representative Concentration Pathways (RCPs) used for climate projections.
dcterms:title: Various climate models and scenarios (e.g., RCP2.6, RCP8.5)
